about.summary: After defining an R6 class, R62S3 is used to automatically generate optional S3/S4 generics and methods for dispatch. Also allows piping for R6 objects.
After defining an R6 class, R62S3 is used to automatically generate optional S3/S4 generics and methods for dispatch. Also allows piping for R6 objects.

name: r-r62s3
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.4.1' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-r62s3
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/R62S3_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/R62S3/R62S3_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: a2c9fbcebfe7b3970be5099d453b10d198b9f37f426d8e7b3af6ea73de8f013c

build:
  number: 4
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-data.table
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-data.table

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('R62S3')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('R62S3')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/RaphaelS1/R62S3/
  license: MIT
  summary: After defining an R6 class, R62S3 is used to automatically generate optional S3/S4
    generics and methods for dispatch. Also allows piping for R6 objects.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT'
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - pascal-git
